******
Asia
----
- Philippines (Metro Manilla). 21 Aug 2011. Health officials expressed
concern yesterday [20 Aug 2011] over an upsurge of dengue cases in the
Philippine capital that has killed 70 people in the 1st 8 months of
the year [2011]. The Department of Health said dengue cases in
Metropolitan Manila from 1 Jan - 6 Aug [2011] rose to 10 487 compared
to 5416 cases for the same period last year [2010].
http://www.gulftimes.com/site/topics/article.asp?cu_no=2&item_no=453799&version=1&template_id=46&parent_id=26

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Manila can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/19Mw. - Mod.TY]

******
- Philippines (Muntinlupa, Metro Manila). 16 Aug 2011. The local
government of Muntinlupa City [the southernmost city in the Philippine
National Capital Region] today [16 Aug 2011] declared a dengue
outbreak due to an alarming increase in the number of cases in the
city. Muntinlupa Mayor Aldrin San Pedro said that based on the local
health office's records, the total number of dengue cases recorded in
the city from 1 Jan - 5 Aug this year [2011] has increased to 258, a
370 per cent increase compared to last year's [2010] 59 cases. San
Pedro also reported that a total of 5 patients have died from dengue.

http://www.philstar.com/nation/article.aspx?publicationsubcategoryid=200&articleid=71734

[A map of Muntinlupa, Metro Manila can be accessed at
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muntinlupa. - Mod.TY]

******
- Philippines (Aklan province, Western Visayas). 20 Aug 2011. From 1
Jan - 15 Aug this year [2011], 121 dengue cases have been listed by
the Provincial Health Office (PHO). This record, according to Dr.
Cornelio V. Cuachon, Jr., Provincial Health Officer I, is 75 per cent
lower compared with last year's [2010] 477 cases for the same period.

http://www.pia.gov.ph/?m=1&t=1&id=50050

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Aklan province, Western
Visayas can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/07gd. - Mod.TY]

******
- India (Orissa state). 20 Aug 2011. The death toll due to dengue has
risen to 19 from 17 with 2 more deaths reported today [20 Aug 2011].
Up to today (20 Aug 2011), a total of 482 samples have been found
positive out of a total 1163 samples tested.
http://orissadiary.com/CurrentNews.asp?id=28656

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Orissa state can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/07gd. - Mod.TY]

******
- Pakistan (Faisalabad, Punjab province). 17 Aug 2011. Health
officials have confirmed that 2 dengue patients have been admitted to
the local Allied Hospital. A teaching institution of the Punjab
Medical College has also stated that 8 similar cases have been
reported from rural areas, where they are seeking treatment from
private clinics. "We have begun to get confirmed reports of the virus,
and we have already placed all DHQ hospitals on alert. Vaccines are
being ordered," said Dr Azhar Rauf [This is an odd statement; no
commercial dengue virus vaccines are available. - Mod.TY].
http://tribune.com.pk/story/233156/health-alert-10-cases-of-dengue-detected/

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Faisalabad, Punjab
province can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/19Mu. - Mod.TY]

******
- Pakistan (Lahore, Punjab province). 16 Aug 2011. On Tuesday [16 Aug
2011], 24 dengue cases were reported in Lahore, bringing the total
number of reported dengue cases to 91. According to the Punjab Health
Department, 27 fresh cases were reported from across the province. Out
of these, 24 were from Lahore, 2 from Faisalabad and one from
Muzaffargarh.
http://tribune.com.pk/story/232806/dengue-epidemic-cases-rise-to-91/

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Lahore, Punjab province
can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/19Mt. - Mod.TY]

******
- Pakistan (Karachi, Sindh province). 16 Aug 2011. The Sindh Health
Department has confirmed 6 more dengue virus cases in Karachi this
week. In charge of Sindh Health Department's Dengue Surveillance Cell,
Dr Suresh Kumar said that out of these 6 dengue fever cases, 2
patients have recovered, while 4 others are under treatment in
different hospitals. He said that 14 new cases of dengue fever have
been confirmed this month [August 2011]. He further reported that out
of 142 suspected dengue patients, 138 have been confirmed positive in
the province this year [2011].
http://www.thenews.com.pk/NewsDetail.aspx?ID=20811&title=Six-new-dengue-cases-confirmed-in-Khi

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Karachi, Sindh province
can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/05Pd. - Mod.TY]

******
Latin America
---
- Brazil (Ribeirao Preto, Sao Paulo State). 17 Aug 2011. In one month,
the number of dengue cases increased from 15 325 to 16 240. The number
of deaths has not changed, remaining at 12.
http://www.ribeiraopretoonline.com.br/saude/ribeirao-preto-registra-915-novos-br--casos-de-dengue-em-um-mes/44225

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Ribeirao Preto, Sao Paulo
state can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/0IpF. - Mod.TY]
